Vendored MediaPipe Face Detection model — full-range BlazeFace, ONNX float
========================================================================

Used by `js/ops/faceDetect.js` for the "Detect faces" auto-redact feature
(see docs/plans/2026-05-22-face-detect-design.md for the full design).

Files
-----

- face_detector.onnx      — ONNX graph definition          (~78 KB)
- face_detector.data      — external float weights         (~517 KB)
- qualcomm-metadata.json  — input/output spec from Qualcomm (~3 KB)

The ONNX file references the .data file via the standard external-data
mechanism; ORT Web loads both transparently when they live in the same
directory.

Source
------

Direct re-distribution of the float ONNX export from Qualcomm's
AI Hub Models repo:

  https://huggingface.co/qualcomm/MediaPipe-Face-Detection
  → release_assets.json points at:
  https://qaihub-public-assets.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/qai-hub-models/
    models/mediapipe_face/releases/v0.54.0/mediapipe_face-onnx-float.zip

The zip also bundles a face_landmark_detector — we DON'T vendor that one
(we only need bboxes to draw redact rectangles; landmarks would be ~2.4 MB
of dead weight).

