Verification
------------

Pinned SHA-256 hashes (also enforced by scripts/install-blazeface.mjs):

  face_detector.onnx
    7455604fc33f56a5f90b9489ef0fc30d8d8921c23b03ac1c74b95c9a2eb47108

  face_detector.data
    990a8bec20de1515437cafdae3f5debbc6961ae3e2e6e9f78522853c036d618c

If you re-vendor (e.g. to grab a newer Qualcomm release), update both the
SHAs in this file AND the version string in install-blazeface.mjs.

Model spec
----------

Input:
  image           (1, 3, 256, 256)  float32, range [0, 1], RGB

Outputs (full-range BlazeFace, 896 anchors total over two strides):
  box_coords_1    (1, 512, 16)  — stride 16, 16×16 grid × 2 anchors/cell
  box_coords_2    (1, 384, 16)  — stride 32,  8×8 grid × 6 anchors/cell
  box_scores_1    (1, 512,  1)  — confidence logits per anchor
  box_scores_2    (1, 384,  1)  — confidence logits per anchor

Each row in box_coords is 16 floats: 4 bbox (cx_offset, cy_offset, w, h)
+ 12 landmark offsets (6 keypoints × 2). NMS is NOT baked in — see
faceDetect.js for the decode + NMS pipeline.
